<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Poland. Olkusz, 1922, R. Kobendza, s.n. (holotype, WA0000071422!).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wierzbicka, Pielich. &amp; Wasowicz" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Biscutella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Biscutella laevigata subsp. woycickii" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="laevigata" subSpecies="woycickii">Biscutella laevigata subsp. woycickii</taxonomicName>
is similar to subsp. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Biscutella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. gracilis" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="laevigata" subSpecies="gracilis">gracilis</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the latter in having thin, light-green rosette leaves very densely covered by simple non-glandular trichomes. Plants belonging to subsp. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wierzbicka, Pielich. &amp; Wasowicz" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Biscutella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. woycickii" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="laevigata" subSpecies="woycickii">woycickii</taxonomicName>
have smaller seeds and are characterised by the ability to tolerate and accumulate high quantities of heavy metals.
</paragraph>
